p%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20like%20the%20Israelites%20leaving%20Egypt.%20We%20were%20exhausted%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Sharvit%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Escape%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20been%20five%20hours%20since%20the%20couple%20and%20other%20survivors%20from%20the%20festival%20had%20started%20running.%20It%20was%2011%3A20%20am%20when%20they%20reached%20another%20settlement%20where%20a%20couple%20took%20them%20in%20and%20gave%20them%20food%2C%20water%2C%20and%20respite%20from%20the%20death%20chase.%20At%2014%3A50%20pm%2C%20Israeli%20authorities%2C%20in%20combat%20and%20rescue%20mode%2C%20arranged%20a%20shuttle%20that%20would%20take%20them%20to%20Be'er%20Sheva%2C%20a%20city%20in%20southern%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20still%20in%20the%20Gaza%20envelope%2C%20and%20we%20were%20worried%20about%20the%20rockets%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20arrived%20in%20Be'er%20Sheva%20safely.%20Our%20parents%20came%20to%20pick%20us%20up%20and%20take%20us%20home.%20My%20two%20friends%20who%20had%20been%20with%20me%20at%20the%20party%20were%20also%20rescued.%20They%20had%20been%20hiding%20under%20a%20bush%20for%20four%20hours.%20They%20had%20seen%20people%20being%20killed%20and%20kidnapped%20next%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20all%20so%20grateful%20to%20be%20alive.%20We%20went%20out%20to%20a%20party%2C%20and%20we%20came%20back%20with%20tears%20in%20our%20eyes.%20We%20saw%20friends%20die.%20We%20saw%20families%20destroyed.%20It%20was%20an%20apocalypse.%20The%20terrorists%20came%20to%20kill%20us.%20They%20came%20to%20annihilate%20us.%20But%20we%20survived%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20attack%2C%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20declared%20a%20%26quot%3Bstate%20of%20war%26quot%3B%20and%20vowed%20%26quot%3Bthough%20Israel%20did%20not%20start%20this%20war%26quot%3B%20it%20%26quot%3Bwill%20finish%20it%26quot%3B.%20Israel%20has%20amassed%20