21-AM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3ECaravan%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Emagazine%20has%20won%20the%202023%20Shorenstein%20Journalism%20Award%2C%20sponsored%20by%20Stanford%20University%E2%80%99s%20Shorenstein%20Asia-Pacific%20Research%20Center%2C%20for%20its%20%E2%80%9Csteadfast%20coverage%20that%20champions%20accountability%20and%20media%20independence%20in%20the%20face%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20backsliding%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20award%2C%20which%20carries%20a%20cash%20prize%20of%20%2410%2C000%2C%20recognises%20outstanding%20journalists%20and%20news%20organisations%20for%20excellence%20in%20coverage%20of%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20region.%20Previous%20winners%20of%20the%20award%20include%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20founding%20editor%20Siddharth%20Varadarajan%2C%20%3Cem%3ERappler%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efounding%20editor%20Maria%20Ressa%2C%20investigative%20journalist%20Tom%20Wright%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20Anna%20Fifield%20and%20independent%20journalist%20Ian%20Johnson.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20announcement%20of%20the%20award%2C%20the%20Shorenstein%20Center%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20decline%20in%20press%20freedom%20and%20growing%20threats%20to%20democratic%20institutions%20in%20India%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%20have%20been%20well-documented.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20violence%20against%20journalists%2C%20the%20politically%20partisan%20media%2C%20and%20the%20concentration%20of%20media%20ownership%20all%20demonstrate%20that%20press%20freedom%20is%20in%20crisis%20in%20%E2%80%98the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20democracy%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%E2%80%99%20latest%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frsf.org%2Fen%2Fcountry%2Findia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Press%20Freedom%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20ranks%20India%20as%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20dangerous%20countries%20for%20the%20media.%E2%80%9D%20In%20this%20environment%2C%20where%20media%20organizations%20are%20under%20constant%20pressure%20to%20toe%20the%20government%20line%20and%20critical%20reporting%20is%20often%20suppressed%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20kept%20its%20commitment%20to%20editorial%20independence.%20Facing%20violence%2C%20sedition%20charges%2C%20and%20imprisonment%2C%20the%20magazine%20has%20continued%20to%20produce%20investigations%20exposing%20Hindu%20extremist%20terrorism%2C%20political%20assassinations%2C%20gender%20and%20caste%20inequality%2C%20and%20ethnic%20violence%20against%20the%20Muslim%20minority%20in%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECaravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20editor%20Hartosh%20Singh%20Bal%20delivered%20a%20keynote%20address%20at%20the%20Stanford%20Alumni%20Centre%20in%20California%20on%20October%2010.%20The%20award%20committee%20had%20also%20specifically%20spoken%20of%20Bal%E2%80%99s%20achievements%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20award%20also%20recognizes%20the%20contributions%20of%3Cem%3E%C2%A0The%20Caravan%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3Es%20executive%20editor%2C%20Hartosh%20Singh%20Bal%2C%20who%20formerly%20worked%20as%20the%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20political%20editor%20for%20ten%20years.%20An%20incisive%20commentator%20on%20Indian%20politics%20and%20society%2C%20Bal%20was%20the%20political%20editor%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EOpen%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0magazine%20and%20has%20worked%20with%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%2C%C2%A0Tehelka%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMail%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EWaters%20Close%20Over%20Us%2C%20A%20Journey%20Along%20the%20Narmada%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20co-author%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EA%20Certain%20Ambiguity%2C%20A%20Mathematical%20Novel%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20is%20trained%20as%20an%20engineer%20and%20a%20mathematician.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696994753000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fw