direct%2F6532f311-fe9a-40bf-87b4-f92b80d2e94f%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1697078527632000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw30WVp5wc2jaOIgKxkWDE-L%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20and%20evaluate%20the%2010%20vulnerable%20glacial%20lakes%20in%20Sikkim%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20to%20work%20out%20appropriate%20mitigation%20strategies%20against%20GLOF.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20state%20and%20national%20authorities%20knew%20that%20South%20Lhonak%20glacial%20lake%20is%20highly%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20GLOF%20event%20because%20the%2060%20metre%20high%2C%201200%20MW%20Teesta%203%20Hydroelectric%20Project%20is%20only%2050%20km%20downstream%20as%20the%20crow%20flies.%20But%20the%20flash%20floods%20triggered%20on%20the%20night%20of%20October%203-4%20showed%20that%20there%20was%20no%20early%20warning%20issued%20in%20time%20to%20downstream%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20account%20on%20page%2073%20of%20the%20CAG%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Performance%20Audit%20on%20Schemes%20for%20Flood%20Control%20and%20Flood%20Forecasting%E2%80%99%20(Report%20No%2010%20of%202017)%20shows%20how%20much%20of%20Sikkim%20is%20flood%20prone.%20In%20its%20territory%20of%207.10%20lakh%20hectares%2C%20in%201976%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Barh%20Aayog%20found%20that%200.00%20lakh%20hectares%20are%20flood%20prone%20areas%20(FPA)!%20The%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20FPA%20estimate%20is%200.20%20lakh%20hectares.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20region%2C%20which%20is%20home%20to%20several%20glacial%20lakes%2C%20whose%20GLOF%20hazards%20were%20known%20to%20glacier%20experts%2C%20used%20to%20under-estimate%20its%20susceptibility%20to%20floods%20until%20the%20mid-1970s!%20However%2C%20with%20increased%20development%20activities%20and%20the%20mania%20for%20hydropower%20that%20engulfed%20the%20state%20in%20the%20last%2020%20years%2C%20GLOF-triggered%20flash%20floods%20are%20a%20very%20real%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20CAG%20audit%20report%20further%20said%20this%20on%20GLOFs%2C%20on%20page%2080%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20work%20on%20monitoring%20glacial%20lakes%20in%20the%20Himalayan%20region%20was%20taken%20up%20by%20CWC%20in%202009.%20The%20inventory%20of%20Glacial%20Lakes%20was%20prepared%20in%202011%20based%20on%20satellite%20images%20taken%20in%202009.%20As%20per%20inventory%20there%20were%202027%20glacial%20lakes%2Fwater%20bodies%20%3E%2010%20h.%20area.%20Since%202011%2C%20monitoring%20of%20only%20477%20glacial%20lakes%2F%20water%20bodies%20having%20water%20spread%20of%20more%20than%2050%20h.%20was%20done%20every%20year%20during%20monsoon%20(June%20to%20October).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECAG%20auditors%20should%20have%20pressed%20the%20Central%20Water%20Commission%20to%20make%20available%20for%20audit%20all%20the%20monitoring%20reports%20of%20these%20glacial%20lakes%2C%20or%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20of%20them%20that%20have%20been%20identified%20as%20most%20vulnerable.%20CAG%20auditors%20appear%20to%20have%20not%20investigated%20the%20preparedness%20for%20GLOF%20and%20the%20monitoring%20of%20glacial%20lakes%20beyond%20accepting%20CWC%E2%80%99s%20claims%20at%20face%20value.%20Had%20they%20consulted%20a%20person%20who%20lived%20in%20Sikkim%20on%20a%20glacier-fed%20watercourse%2C%20they%20would%20have%20encountered%20a%20different%20level%20of%20urgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Sikkim%20Disaster%3A%20Were%20Successive%20Alarm%20Bells%20Ignored%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsikkim-disaster-flood-warning%5C%22%3ESikkim%20Disaster%3A%20Were%20Successive%20Alarm%20Bells%20Ignored%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20story%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EScroll%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fcbf97591-47e3-4f16-ac33-06adb8f657e6%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fcbf97591-47e3-4f16-ac33-06adb8f657e6%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1697078527632000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3Nead0zRvNn2ssIppW93Y7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECWC%20officials%20claim%20that%20glacial%20lakes%20that%20pose%20the%20risk%20of%20GLOF%20are%20monitoring%20through%20satellite%20data%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20this%20claim%20is%20true%2C%20among%20the%20records%20there%20must%20be%20a%20report%20on%20the%20South%20Lhonak%20Glacial%20Lake%20for%20September.%20Satellite%20images%20released%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20by%20ISRO%20show%20that%20the%20South%20Lhonak%20Lake%20grew%20by%203%25%20on%2011-28%20September.%20Was%20this%20analysed%20in%20the%20monitoring%20report%20for%20September%20and%20communicated%20with%20the%20Sikkim%20State%20Disaster%20Management%20Authority%20as%20a%20heads-up%20for%20an%20impending%20disaster%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20from%20a%20senior%20civil%20servant%20working%20in%20Sikkim%20shows%20that%20there%20was%20no%20coordination%20even%20hours%20after%20the%20South%20Lhonak%20Lake%20had%20burst%20its%20banks.%20He%20writes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20order%20to%20open%20gates%20of%20Dikchu%20Dam%20was%20given%20at%202.00%20AM%20in%20the%20morning%20of%204%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0October%202023.%20Only%20when%20the%20floodwaters%20had%20already%20hit%20Dikchu%20Dam.%20So%2C%20when%20the%20Chungthang%20Dam%20breached%20the%20information%20was%20not%20available%20at%20(the%20downstream)%20Dikchu%20dam.%20Which%20means%20the%20early%20warning%20system%20was%20not%20in%20place.%20There%20was%20no%20notified%20chain%20of%20commands.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Twitter%20thread%2C%20Kerala-based%20civil%20engineer%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F437f1831-ad7a-48da-8f85-23df62e5616d%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F437f1831-ad7a-48da-8f85-23df62e5616d%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1697078527632000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1wBiqMZHibKHeNKGs0kQpK%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJames%20Wilson%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0states%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20CWC%20Advisory%20Sheet%20on%20GLOF%20%E2%80%93%20South%20Lhonak%20Glacial%20Lake%20of%202015.%20CWC%20identified%20South%20Lhonak%20Lake%20as%20a%20potential%20hazard%20with%20an%20estimated%20area%20of%20136%20hectares%20and%20having%20water%20volume%20of%2040.8%20Million%20Cubic%20Metre%20in%20the%20year%202015%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20a%20highly%20sophisticated%20mathematical%20model%20(MIKE-11)%20employed%20by%20CWC%20to%20estimate%20the%20GLOF%20generated%20runoff%20found%20that%20if%20the%20South%20Lhonak%20Lake%20had%20burst%20in%20the%202015%20monsoons%2C%20it%20would%20have%20drained%20out%206%2C210%20cubic%20metres%20of%20water%20per%20second%20in%20two%20hours!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAffected%20communities%20downstream%20are%20busy%20organising%20relief.%20They%20feel%20that%20this%20disaster%20shall%20not%20be%20passed%20off%20as%20yet%20another%20flash%20flood%20following%20a%20cloudburst.%20They%20feel%20that%20tough%20questions%20will%20be%20asked%20about%20the%20cascading%20effect%20of%20a%20series%20of%20hydropower%20dams%20that%20were%20constructed%2C%20throwing%20the%20concerns%20raised%20by%20geologists%20to%20the%20winds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20the%20risks%20of%20South%20Lhonak%20GLOF%20and%20what%20SSDMA%20was%20doing%20on%20the%20mitigation%20front%20was%20known%20only%20bureaucratic%20circles.%20However%2C%20local%20communities%20downstream%20were%20not%20kept%20informed%20about%20the%20risks%20generated%20by%20a%20likely%20event%20of%20a%20GLOF%20at%20South%20Lhonak%20or%20Shako%20Cho%20glacial%20lakes%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mona%20Chhetri%2C%20a%20researcher%20based%20in%20Gangtok.%20She%20feels%20that%20in%20the%20discussions%20and%20conversations%20after%20the%20Teesta%20flash%20floods%2C%20the%20role%20played%20by%20downstream%20hydropower%20dams%20is%20crucially%20missing.%20She%20adds%20that%20it%20might%20have%20been%20triggered%20by%20a%20natural%20disaster%20such%20as%20GLOF%2C%20but%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20Early%20Warning%20System%20and%20the%20failure%20to%20open%20the%20dam%20gates%20at%20Teesta%203%20Hydropower%20Dam%20needs%20to%20be%20talked%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20even%20as%20this%20GLOF-triggered%20flash%20flood%20was%20knocking%20at%20their%20doors%2C%20the%20Sikkim%20bureaucracy%20was%20busy%20issuing%20gazette%20notification%20to%20acquire%20land%20from%20farmers%20to%20construct%20yet%20another%20hydropower%20dam%20on%20the%20Teesta%20River%20basin%2C%20namely%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F38a4a4e3-09c0-41c7-8632-cf865c3ab3f1%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F38a4a4e3-09c0-41c7-8632-cf865c3ab3f1%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1697078527632000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1HLX_jkZQHRKma1B5W26cK%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E520%20MW%20Teesta%20IV%20Hydroelectric%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fd92cfc90-273b-48c8-9fde-d6fe41cf7288%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data