r%20eggs%20will%20have%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20drowning%20in%20a%20flood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20timing%20seemed%20right%2C%20and%20the%20sound%20and%20vibrations%20from%20the%20chopper%20may%20have%20mimicked%20a%20thunderstorm%20signaling%20to%20the%20male%20crocs%20that%20it%20was%20go%20time.%20The%20motion%20of%20the%20Chinook's%20blades%20may%20have%20also%20caused%20changes%20in%20the%20barometric%20pressure%20similar%20to%20a%20storm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%2C%20another%20theory%2C%20is%20that%20the%20crocodiles%20may%20have%20mistaken%20the%20helicopter's%20roar%20for%20the%20bellows%20and%20splashing%20tails%20of%20other%20males%2C%20O'Shea%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20cause%2C%20the%20next%20step%20will%20be%20for%20the%20female%20crocodiles%20to%20make%20nests%20for%20their%20eggs.%20Using%20soil%20and%20rotting%20vegetation%2C%20they%20create%20mounds%20where%20dozens%20of%20eggs%20incubate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20about%20three%20months%2C%20the%20mothers%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcambodian-farmer-killed-40-crocodiles-2023-5%5C%22%3Eaggressively%20protect%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20eggs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELever's%20farm%20has%20about%203%2C000%20of%20the%20reptiles%2C%20which%20he%20raises%20for%20their%20meat%20and%20leather%20and%20as%20a%20tourist%20attraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrocodiles-helicopter-mating-frenzy-sound-thunderstorm-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696978798000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525ce9568f1d46f52ade240%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrocodiles-helicopter-mating-frenzy-sound-thunderstorm-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Chinook%20helicopter%20flew%20over%20a%20crocodile%20farm%2C%20prompting%20a%20mating%20frenzy%20among%20