0but%20medium-caliber%20cannons%20on%20other%20armored%20vehicles%20can%20be%20just%20as%20deadly.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThose%20smaller%20cannons%20have%20%26quot%3Bshaped%20combat%26quot%3B%20for%20both%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20one%20expert%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20tanks%20and%20their%20big%20guns%20have%20been%20getting%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20attention%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20another%20weapon%20is%20proving%20equally%20deadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium-caliber%20cannon%20%E2%80%94%20the%2020-mm%20to%2040-mm%20cannon%20found%20on%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%2C%20air-defense%20vehicles%2C%20and%20other%20platforms%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20wreaking%20damage%20against%20infantry%20and%20other%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%2C%20both%20sides%20are%20using%20Soviet-era%202A42%2030-mm%20autocannon%20that%20are%20outfitted%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-puts-russian-made-armored-vehicle-flaws-on-display-2023-10%5C%22%3Ethe%20Russian-designed%20vehicles%20used%20by%20both%20armies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20BMP-2%2C%20BMP-3%20and%20BMD-4M%20troop%20carriers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Ukrainian%20versions%20of%20the%20BTR-3%20and%20BTR-4%2C%20land-warfare%20expert%20Sam%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuro-sd.com%2F2023%2F01%2Farticles%2F29152%2Flessons-from-ukraine-armoured-fighting-vehicles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Security%20and%20Defence%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20BTR-82A%20armored%20personnel%20carrier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525943955f52b01b35b5c00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221411%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20BTR-82A%20in%20the%20Victory%20Day%20military%20parade%20in%20Red%20Square%20in%20June%202020.%3Cp%3EVladimir%20Pesnya%2FHost%20Photo%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20cannons%20are%20in%20widespread%20use%2C%20have%20%26quot%3Bferocious%26quot%3B%20firepower%2C%20and%20they%20have%20%26quot%3Bshaped%20combat%26quot%3B%20for%20both%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20wrote%20Cranny-Evans%2C%20who%20previously%20was%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECranny-Evans%20cited%20a%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20who%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.facebook.com%2FMilitary_Footage-1644786445778987%2Fvideos%2Frussian-btrsrussian-btr-vehicles-i-think-are-worse-than-tanks-the-gun-on-them-fi%2F505215791176244%2F%3F_se_imp%3D0D5YlchsykRLkhHQ0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplained%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20Russian%20armored%20personnel%20carriers%20%26quot%3Bare%20worse%20than%20tanks.%20The%20gun%20on%20them%20fires%20faster%20and%20they%20carry%20soldiers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWounds%20from%20these%20are%20horrible.%20A%20whole%20leg%20can%20be%20removed.%20A%20shot%20to%20the%20body%20makes%20someone%20almost%20explode%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Russian%20APCs%20%26quot%3Bare%20easy%20to%20destroy%20but%20not%20good%20to%20fight%20directly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium-caliber%20cannon%20can%20engage%20infantry%20from%20a%20distance%20or%20even%20damage%20a%20tank%20%E2%80%94%20both%20of%20which%20are%20uses%20observed%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20it%20is%20apparent%20that%20infantry%20formations%20fare%20poorly%20against%20cannons%20if%20they%20are%20not%20supported%2C%26quot%3B%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20also%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20urban%20warfare%20as%20they%20are%20capable%20of%20suppressing%20positions%20from%20ranges%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20beyond%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20standard%20shoulder-fired%20anti-armor%20weapons%20carried%20by%20infantry%20formations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20BMP-2%20armored%20amphibious%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525c20955f52b01b35bb3ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222494%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPersonnel%20load%20the%20gun%20of%20a%20BMP-2%20amphibious%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%20during%20an%20arms%20exhibition%20Russia%20in%20September%202013.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FSergei%20Karpukhin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20instinctively%20view%20the%20biggest%20cannon%20as%20the%20best%20in%20terms%20of%20firepower%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20that%20straightforward.%20A%20main%20battle%20tank%20like%20the%20US-made%20M-1%20or%20the%20Soviet-designed%20T-72%20are%20armed%20with%20120-mm%20or%20125-mm%20guns%20that%20can%20destroy%20other%20tanks%20from%20miles%20away.%20But%20those%20tanks%20carry%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20cannon%20rounds%20and%20their%20main%20guns%20have%20a%20limited%20rate%20of%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20their%20main%20guns%20are%20ill-suited%20for%20many%20targets%20on%20the%20battlefield.%20During%20World%20War%20II%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fww2armor%2Fposts%2Fnow-hear-thiswhat-main-gun-ammunition-was-carried-by-the-m4-sherman-tanks-with-t%2F328151730865334%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E80%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20targets%20engaged%20by%20the%20M4%20Sherman%20tank%20were%20soft%20targets%20such%20as%20infantry%2C%20anti-tank%20guns%2C%20and%20bunkers.%20To%20send%20tanks%20after%20dispersed%20targets%20like%20infantry%20is%20like%20hunting%20rabbits%20with%20a%20howitzer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20tanks%20have%20machine%20guns%20in%20the%2012.7-mm%20and%207.62-mm%20range%2C%20to%20engage%20personnel%20or%20to%20hit%20soft%20vehicles%2C%20such%20as%20trucks%2C%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20big%20cannon%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium-caliber%2C%20rapid-fire%20cannon%2C%20such%20as%20the%20M242%20Bushmaster%2025-mm%20chain%20gun%20on%20the%20US's%20M2%20Bradley%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%2C%20combine%20a%20rate%20of%20fire%20like%20that%20of%20a%20machine%20gun%20with%20the%20heavier%20shells%20used%20by%20a%20cannon.%20The%202A42%20can%20pump%20out%20up%20500%20rounds%20a%20minute%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-tulamash-ru.translate.goog%2Fcatalog%2F15%3F_x_tr_sl%3Dauto%26_x_tr_tl%3Den%26_x_tr_hl%3Den-US%26_x_tr_sch%3Dhttp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E27A2%3C%2Fa%3E%20model%20can%20shoot%20330%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20Bradley%20armored%20Fighting%20vehicle%20M240%20machine%20gun%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525b9b86561dd877e76af3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20fire%20the%20M240C%20coaxial%20machine%20gun%20on%20a%20Bradley%20Fighting%20Vehicle%20during%20an%20exercise%20in%20Lithuania%20in%20November%202014.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Keith%20Anderson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20weapons%20can%20also%20fire%20a%20variety%20of%20ammunition%2C%20including%20armor-piercing%20and%20high-explosive%20rounds.%20The%20M242%20Bushmaster%20can%20even%20fire%20depleted-uranium%20shells%20against%20tanks.%20Bradleys%20famously%20used%20their%2025-mm%20guns%20to%20suppress%20Iraqi%20T-72%20tanks%2C%20buying%20them%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcoffeeordie.com%2Fbradley-headed-to-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edestroy%20the%20Iraqi%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20M2's%20TOW%20anti-tank%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%2C%20if%20they%20have%20a%20choice%2C%20should%20pick%20a%20fight%20with%20heavily%20armored%20tanks%2C%20but%20medium%20cannon%20have%20proven%20their%20value.%20Britain%20found%2030-mm%20cannon%20useful%20in%20the%20Falklands%2C%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20these%20weapons%20%26quot%3Bwere%20also%20used%20as%20a%20form%20of%20precision%20direct%20fire%20in%20Afghanistan%20where%20they%20served%20to%20quickly%20suppress%20Taliban%20forces%2C%20and%20similar%20outcomes%20have%20been%20reported%20by%20French%20forces%20fighting%20in%20Mali.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20common%20for%20infantry%20fighting%20and%20reconnaissance%20vehicles%20to%20carry%20guns%20that%20would%20have%20been%20the%20main%20armament%20of%20tanks%20in%20the%20early%20years%20of%20World%20War%20II.%20Future%20vehicles%20will%20still%20probably%20be%20armed%20with%20medium%20cannon%2C%20though%20with%20some%20innovations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20M2A3%20Bradley%20Fighting%20Vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65259cf868f1d46f52ad8f1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20M2A3%20Bradley%20Fighting%20Vehicle%20at%20a%20range%20in%20New%20Mexico%20in%20August%202018.%3Cp%3EFort%20Bliss%20Public%20Affairs%2FWinifred%20Brown%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Russia%20are%20looking%20at%20heavier%2050-mm%20or%2057-mm%20guns%20that%20use%20special%20ammunition%20such%20as%20the%20Supershot%2C%20while%20cased%20telescoped%20cannon%20offer%20the%20prospect%20of%20smaller%20and%20lighter%20weapons.%20The%20US%20Army%20also%20plans%20to%20arm%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdefense-update.com%2F20210604_mcws.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStryker%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%2030-mm%20gun%2C%20while%20France%20and%20Britain%20have%20ordered%20BAE's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.baesystems.com%2Fen%2Fproduct%2Fcased-telescoped-cannon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40-mm%20Cased%20Telescoped%20Cannon%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20light%20armored%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20NATO%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20China%20(which%20copies%20Russian%20weapons)%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuro-sd.com%2F2023%2F01%2Farticles%2F29124%2Fmedium-calibre-weapons-back-to-the-future%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20largely%20using%3C%2Fa%3E%20medium-caliber%20cannon%20designed%20in%20the%201970s.%20As%20Russia%20is%20still%20using%20Cold%20War-era%20armored%20vehicles%20vulnerable%20to%20NATO's%20current%20medium%20cannon%20%E2%80%94%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-puts-russian-made-armored-vehicle-flaws-on-display-2023-10%5C%22%3Ethose%20Soviet-designed%20vehicles'%20many%20flaws%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20there%20may%20not%20be%20much%20impetus%20among%20Western%20militaries%20to%20develop%20new%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20become%20a%20laboratory%20to%20demonstrate%20what%20happens%20when%20modern%20mechanized%20armies%20meet%20in%20battle.%20The%20effectiveness%20of%20medium-caliber%20cannons%20suggest%20that%20as%20armored%20vehicles%20evolve%2C%20those%20guns%20will%20remain%20part%20of%20their%20armament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20in%20political%20science.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22a48008f66dd60e4ae3cb2319a8aa10eb%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck