%20(NALSA)%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20case%20in%20April%20next%20year%2C%20we%20should%20look%20at%20the%20problems%20in%20the%20representation%20of%20marginalities%20and%20the%20role%20played%20by%20the%20empty%20rhetoric%20of%20analogies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20opening%20paragraph%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20states%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%5BO%5Dur%20society%20often%20ridicules%20and%20abuses%20the%20Transgender%20community%20and%20in%20public%20places%20like%20railway%20stations%2C%20bus%20stands%2C%20schools%2C%20workplaces%2C%20malls%2C%20theatres%2C%20hospitals%2C%20they%20are%20sidelined%20and%20treated%20as%20untouchables.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20underlying%20assumption%20of%20this%20analogy%20is%20that%20transgender%20and%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20persons%20are%20two%20marginalised%20groups%20distinct%20from%20each%20other.%20The%20assumption%20fails%20in%20the%20face%20of%20Dalit%20and%20Adivasi%20transgender%20persons%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.roundtableindia.co.in%2Ftransgender-and-caste-lived-experience-transphobia-as-a-form-of-brahminism-an-interview-of-living-smile-vidya%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELiving%20Smile%20Vidya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelanganatoday.com%2Fspecially-abled-kiran-nayak-striving-for-transgender-rights%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKiran%20Nayak%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1055658%2Fmeet-dalit-transgender-activist-grace-banu-who-campaigns-for-reservations-for-transgender-people%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGrace%20Banu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERhetorical%20claims%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98transgender%20persons%20are%20treated%20as%20untouchables%E2%80%99%20imply%20that%20marginalised%20groups%20are%20placed%20in%20mutually%20exclusive%20either-or%20sets.%20The%20emerging%20understanding%20of%20one%20group%20is%20said%20to%20be%20just%20like%20the%20previously%20existing%20understanding%20of%20another.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20%E2%80%9CGay%20is%20the%20new%20black%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20example%20of%20a%20rhetorical%20claim%20that%20set%20apart%20gay%20persons%20from%20black%20persons%2C%20as%20if%C2%A0%20all%20gay%20persons%20were%20posited%20as%20white.%20Not%20only%20was%20this%20empirically%20false%2C%20it%20channelled%20a%20discursive%20understanding%20of%20one%20marginality%20into%20another.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20rhetorical%20claims%20and%20distortions%20are%20amplified%20within%20legal%20movements%C2%A0%20As%20a%20result%2C%20a%20group%20recognised%20as%20discriminated%20against%20is%20disabled%20from%20representing%20a%20newly%20emerging%20group%2C%20also%20discriminated%20against.%20Rhetoric%20and%20analogies%20generate%20blind%20spots%20that%20make%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20transgender%20persons%20invisible%2C%20and%20also%20disable%20their%20representational%20agency%20as%20%E2%80%9Cclass%20representatives.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Untouchable%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20considered%20the%20reality%20of%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20transgender%20persons%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20would%20have%20seen%20an%20overlapping%20function%20of%20caste%2C%20sex%2C%20and%20gender%20categories.%20The%20court%20would%20have%20considered%20some%20of%20the%20similarities%20and%20differences%20between%20the%20emerging%20legal%20understanding%20of%20the%20third%20gender%20and%20the%20existing%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20categories.%20The%20two%20categories%20could%20be%20said%20to%20be%20similar%2C%20because%20both%20gender%20and%20caste%20are%20assigned%20at%20birth.%20They%20are%20different%20because%20gender%20categories%20can%20be%20legally%20changed%2C%20whereas%20the%20SC%20categories%20cannot%20be%20changed.%20This%20characteristic%20has%20significance%20in%20the%20doctrinal%20understanding%20of%20anti-discrimination%20law.%20Some%20categories%20are%20so%20immutable%20that%20the%20discriminated-against%20groups%20cannot%20choose%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20categories%20to%20which%20they%20are%20assigned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20about%20these%20similarities%20and%20differences%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EForemost%2C%20in%20its%20omission%20of%20caste%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20lost%20a%20potential%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20existing%20legal%20discourse%20on%20caste%2C%20class%2C%20and%20affirmative%20action.%20Amid%20other%20post-colonial%20continuities%2C%20the%20legal%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbackwardness%E2%80%9D%20finds%20explicit%20yet%20undefined%20mention%20in%20Article%2016(4)%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20state%20to%20make%20provisions%20for%20reservations%20in%20public%20employment%20in%20the%20favour%20of%20the%20backward%20classes%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20no%20doctrinal%20requirement%20of%20comparing%20transgender%20persons%20with%20untouchables.%20Alarge%20bench%20of%20nine%20judges%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Sawhney%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1992)%20is%20sufficiently%20instructive%20in%20the%20matter%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20necessary%20for%20a%20class%20to%20be%20designated%20as%20a%20backward%20class%20that%20it%20%5Bbe%5D%20situated%20similarly%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%2FScheduled%20Tribes%E2%80%9D%20(Para.%20126).%20Thus%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20demonstrated%20insufficient%20familiarity%20with%2C%20and%20complete%20disregard%20for%2C%20a%20larger%20bench%20and%20a%20precedent%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Sawhney%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Ftransgender-prisoners-india%5C%22%3EMisgendering%2C%20Sexual%20Violence%2C%20Harassment%3A%20What%20it%20Is%20to%20Be%20a%20Transgender%20Person%20in%20an%20Indian%20Prison%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%202014%20also%20did%20not%20explain%20why%20these%20analogies%20were%20being%20made.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWas%20it%20for%20an%20eventual%20recognition%20and%20declaration%20of%20transgender%20persons%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbackward%20class%3F%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWho%20decides%20this%20legal%20status%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbackwardness%2C%E2%80%9D%20how%2C%20and%20to%20what%20effect%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIs%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchability%E2%80%9D%20the%20same%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbackwardness%3F%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDoes%20this%20backwardness%20require%20parity%20of%20status%20with%20persons%20in%20the%20SC%20categories%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWho%20among%20the%20marginalised%20can%20represent%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERather%20than%20inform%20itself%20of%20a%20legal%20discourse%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Sawhney%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1992)%20that%20was%20binding%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20informed%20by%20arguments%20based%20on%20more%20dominant%20frameworks%20of%20caste%2C%20sex%2C%20and%20gender.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20National%20Legal%20Services%20Authority%20(NALSA)%20as%20the%20first%20petitioner%2C%20there%20were%20a%20few%20%E2%80%9Cimpleadment%20applications%2C%E2%80%9D%20including%20one%20from%20a%20Hijra%20activist%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Laxmi%20Narayan%20Tripathy%20%E2%80%93%20a%20name%20that%20discloses%20the%20applicant%E2%80%99s%20caste%20denomination%20as%20Brahmin%2C%20the%20highest%20echelon%20of%20caste-based%20hierarchies.%20This%20is%20significant%20for%20an%20understanding%20of%20how%20certain%20dominant%20segments%20within%20minority%20groups%20were%20privileged%20as%20%E2%80%9Cclass%20representatives%E2%80%9D%20in%20an%20emerging%20legal%20discourse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERegardless%20of%20any%20explicit%20self-identification%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Tripathy%2C%20caste%20associations%20and%20identities%20are%20enmeshed%20and%20encoded%20within%20some%20surnames%20%E2%80%93%20such%20that%20their%20reception%20goes%20beyond%20any%20self-awareness%2C%20declaration%2C%20intent%2C%20and%20consciousness.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHad%20the%20court%20been%20alert%20to%20this%20salience%20of%20caste%20in%20naming%2C%20it%20would%20have%20noted%20a%20contradiction%20of%20sorts%20%E2%80%93%20a%20certain%20reverse%20mobility%20of%20caste-based%20hierarchies%20%E2%80%93%20that%20allowed%20a%20Brahmin%20to%20be%20similarly%20situated%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable.%E2%80%9D%20An%20imminent%20contradiction%20in%20this%20analogy%20is%20especially%20ironic%20in%20a%20caste-based%20hierarchy%20that%20accords%20the%20highest%20stature%20to%20Brahmins%20and%20the%20lowest%20stature%20to%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchables.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20lack%20of%20any%20explicit%20labelling%20or%20signage%20of%20this%20Brahmin%20identity%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20arguments%20of%20Tripathy%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20were%20aligned%20with%20well-known%20Brahmanical%20ideas.%20The%20intervention%20foregrounded%20a%20more%20favourable%20historical%20background%20of%20transgender%20persons%20within%20Hindu%20mythology%2C%20Vedic%2C%20and%20Puranic%20literatures%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%202014%3A%20Para.%206)%2C%20which%20are%20also%20considered%20historically%20exclusive%20knowledge-domains%20of%20the%20Brahmins%20and%20sources%20of%20pervasive%20caste%20and%20gender-based%20inequality%20(such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EManusmriti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20Tripathy%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20made%20references%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20repealed%20Criminal%20Tribes%20Act%2C%201871%20and%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20inhuman%20manner%20by%20which%20they%20were%20treated%20at%20the%20time%20of%20a%20British%20Colonial%20rule%E2%80%9D%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%202014%3A%20Para.%206).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20endorsed%20and%20validated%20these%20arguments%20by%20further%20elaborating%20on%20them%20(2014%3A%20Paras.%2012%E2%80%9317).%20This%20was%20a%20selective%20foregrounding%20of%20the%20ills%20of%20colonial%20oppression%2C%20while%20neglecting%20and%20remaining%20silent%20about%20the%20historic%20ills%20of%20caste-based%20subordination%20and%20inequality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmarriage-equality-legal-recognition%5C%22%3EA%20Trans-Queer%20Paradox%20and%20the%20Search%20for%20Legal%20Recognition%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20level%20of%20a%20failed%20eventual%20outcome%2C%20%3Ci%3ENALSA%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99s%20declaration%20of%20transgender%20persons%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csocially%20and%20educationally%20backward%20class%E2%80%9D%20failed%20to%20be%20recognised%20in%20the%20legislative%20framework%20to%20follow%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupriyo-marriage-equality-supreme-court-solicitor-general%5C%22%3ETransgender%20Persons%20(Protection%20of%20Rights)%20Act%20of%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20perhaps%20because%20the%20identification%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbackward%20classes%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20constitutional%20function%20of%20the%20governments%20at%20the%20federal%20and%20state%20levels%2C%20not%20the%20judiciary.%20In%20an%20eagerness%20to%20declare%20affirmative%20action%20for%20transgender%20persons%2C%20%3Ci%3ENALSA%3C%2Fi%3E%20appropriated%20a%20function%20of%20the%20executive%20branch%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20juridical%20thinking%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20an%20illustration%20of%20an%20analogy%20drawn%20from%20anti-caste%20discourse%20and%20a%20failure%20to%20engage%20with%20that%20discourse.%20Analogies%2C%20and%20assertions%20of%20identities%2C%20must%20engage%20with%20surrounding%20discourses%20for%20an%20improved%20understanding%20of%20marginalization%20and%20for%20generating%20more%20inclusive%20discourses%20on%20matters%20of%20representations%2C%20recognition%2C%20and%20intersectional%20solidarities%20worldwide.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProfessor%20Dr%20Sumit%20Baudh%20(they%20%2Fhe)%20teaches%20Caste%2C%20Law%20and%20Representation%2C%20among%20other%20courses%20and%20sources.%20Views%20in%20this%20article%20are%C2%A0%20drawn%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F14754835.2020.1858402%5C%22%3Elonger%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20an%20academic%20journal.%20He%20tweets%20%40BaudhSumit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696942839000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10160824%2F3667997607_a1f6bde5f8_c.jpg%22