20social%20media%20over%20alleged%20anti-India%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPakistan%20news%20outlet%20%3Cem%3ESamaa%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20Abbas%20left%20India%20citing%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20concerns%E2%80%9D.%20The%20ICC%2C%20however%2C%20clarified%20that%20Abbas%E2%80%99s%20departure%20from%20India%20was%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20reasons%E2%80%9D.%20ICC%20official%20C.%20Rajshekhar%20Rao%20confirmed%20this%20information%20to%20%3Cem%3EArab%20News%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%2035-year-old%20had%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FZAbbasOfficial%2Fstatus%2F1708719707023360331%5C%22%3Eposted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20social%20media%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Chumbled%E2%80%9D%20to%20join%20the%20six-week%20World%20Cup%20coverage%20programme.%20In%20the%20same%20post%2C%20she%20mentioned%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20cultural%20similarities%20than%20differences%E2%80%9D%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20media%20reports%20had%20suggested%20that%20her%20exit%20was%20related%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20following%20a%20complaint%20filed%20in%20Delhi%20by%20a%20lawyer.%20The%20complaint%20filed%20by%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyer%20Vineet%20Jindal%20October%206%20accused%20Abbas%20of%20posting%20%E2%80%9Cderogatory%E2%80%9D%20tweets%20targeting%20the%20Hindu%20faith%2C%20based%20on%20screenshots%20of%20posts%20made%20by%20an%20account%20with%20her%20name%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDated%20October%204%2C%20the%20complaint%20alleged%20that%20Abbas%20had%20made%20statements%20that%20were%20anti-India%20and%20Hinduphobic.%20Jindal%20reported%20the%20complaint%20to%20the%20Cyber%20Cell%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20via%20X%2C%20requesting%20the%20filing%20of%20a%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20against%20Abbas%20under%20Sections%20153A%2C%20295%2C%20506%2C%20121%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20and%20Section%2067%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%20for%20her%20%E2%80%9Cderogatory%20remarks%20about%20Hinduism%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Canti-India%20statements%E2%80%9D.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20lawyer%20demanded%20that%20Abbas%20be%20removed%20as%20a%20presenter%20for%20the%20World%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESamaa%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samaa.tv%2F208732344-pakistani-presenter-zainab-abbas-leaves-india-over-safety-concerns%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Abbas%20denied%20the%20allegations%20and%20maintained%20that%20she%20had%20been%20unjustly%20targeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESports%20and%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPakistani%20fans%20and%20journalists%20have%20been%20facing%20prolonged%20delays%20in%20obtaining%20visas%20to%20attend%20World%20Cup%20matches%20in%20India%2C%20which%20commenced%20last%20week.%20Even%20the%20players%E2%80%99%20visa%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fcricket-world-cup-pakistan-board-flags-delay-by-india-in-granting-visas-to-team-with-icc%5C%22%3Egranted%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%20after%20the%20Pakistan%20Cricket%20Board%20(PCB)%20petitioned%20the%20ICC.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDawn%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20some%20Pakistan%20citizens%20who%20had%20tickets%20for%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20opening%20game%20against%20the%20Netherlands%20could%20not%20attend%20because%20of%20unresolved%20visa%20issues.%20The%20Indian%20high%20commission%2C%20awaiting%20instructions%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20home%20ministry%2C%20has%20not%20yet%20provided%20a%20response%2C%20leaving%20fans%20anxious%20about%20attending%20future%20matches%2C%20including%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20game%20against%20Sri%20Lanka%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAround%2060%20journalists%20from%20Pakistan%20are%20waiting%20to%20get%20a%20visa%20clearance%20from%20Indian%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsport%2Fcricket%2Ficc-world-cup%2Fpakistan-media-fans-still-awaiting-visas-for-world-cup%2Farticle67389744.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESportstar%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20PCB%20source%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CTill%20now%20there%20is%20no%20word%20about%20the%20visas%20and%20the%20World%20Cup%20has%20already%20started.%20This%20is%20not%20what%20we%20expected%2C%20but%20we%20are%20still%20hoping%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20clears%20the%20visas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Zaka%20Ashraf%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20PCB%20Interim%20Management%20Committee%2C%20met%20with%20foreign%20secretary%20Syrus%20Sajjad%20Qazi%20to%20express%20concerns%20about%20the%20delayed%20issuance%20of%20visas%20for%20Pakistani%20fans%20and%20journalists%20who%20want%20to%20travel%20to%20India%20for%20the%20World%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReports%20have%20highlighted%20the%20contrasting%20policies%20of%20other%20sports%20events%20like%20the%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20and%20the%20Olympics%2C%20where%20measures%20are%20in%20place%20to%20facilitate%20easy%20entry%20for%20journalists%20and%20fans.%20For%20example%2C%20during%20the%202018%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%2C%20tournament%20host%20Russia%20introduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2018%2F07%2F26%2Fworld-cup-fans-granted-visa-free-entry-to-russia-under-newly-passed-bill-a62355%5C%22%3Ea%20visa-free%20entry%3C%2Fa%3E%20policy%20for%20fans%20holding%20tickets.%20Journalists%20were%20promptly%20issued%20visas%20on%20the%20spot%20at%20Russian%20consular%20offices.%20Qatar%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fragomen.com%2Finsights%2Fqatar-relaxed-requirements-for-2022-fifa-world-cup-visas.html%5C%22%3Erelaxed%20visa%20requirements%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20World%20Cup%20it%20hosted%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20hope%20remains%2C%20with%20speculation%20suggesting%20that%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20Pakistani%20journalists%20might%20receive%20visas%20before%20the%20much-anticipated%20India-Pakistan%20match%20on%20October%2014.%20However%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20high%20commission%20in%20Pakistan%20has%20deepened%20concerns.%20Former%20PCB%20chief%20Ehsan%20Mani%20called%20for%20the%20Pakistani%20team%E2%80%99s%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20World%20Cup%20if%20visas%20are%20not%20issued%20to%20fans%20and%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696941931000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10180840%2FF5-F4WVbUAAAV0z.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fcricket-world-cup-pakistani-presenter-zainab-abbas-leaves-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lawyer%20Vineet%20Jindal's%20complaint%20accused%20Zainab%20Abbas%20of%20posting%20%26quot%3Bderogatory%26quot%3B%20tweets%20targeting%20the%20Hindu%20faith%2C%20based%20on%20screenshots%20of%20posts%20made%20by%20an%20account%20with%20her%20name%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20in%202014.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A53%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fcricket-world-cup-pakistani-presenter-zainab-abbas-leaves-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vidarbha%20Literary%20Festival%20Curators%2C%20Organiser%20Step%20Down%20After%20'Right-Wing%20Threats'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10163925%2Fbanner-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20three%20curators%20and%20organisers%20of%20the%20Vidarbha%20Literary%20Festival%20have%20stepped%20down%2C%20allegedly%20after%20right-wing%20activists%20began%20threatening%20them%20and%20their%20family%20members.%20The%20festival%2C%20exclusively%20catering%20to%20non-fiction%20writings%20and%20started%20just%20months%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020%2C%20is%20scheduled%20to%20have%20its%20next%20edition%20in%20February%202024.%20But%20curators%20Sukhada%20Chaudhary%20and%20Pawan%20Sarda%20and%20organiser%20Ruta%20Dharamadhikari%20collectively%20decided%20to%20step%20down%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESources%20privy%20to%20the%20developments%20at%20the%20festival%20said%20that%20activists%20belonging%20to%20right-wing%20organisations%20raised%20objection%20over%20four%20of%20the%20many%20speakers%20who%20were%20invited%20to%20the%20festival.%20The%20objection%20was%20against%20inviting%20journalists%20and%20authors%20like%20Aakar%20Patel%2C%20Josy%20Joseph%2C%20Shruti%20Ganpataye%20and%20Shivam%20Shankar%20Singh%20to%20the%20festival.%20For%20the%20February%202024%20edition%2C%20around%2040%20speakers%20were%20invited.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPatel%2C%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20recently%20came%20out%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FAakar-Patel%2Fe%2FB075J9J5TN%2Fref%3Ddp_byline_cont_book_1%5C%22%3Ebooks%20that%20focus%20on%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20BJP%20government%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Investigative%20journalist%20and%20author%20Joseph%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Silent%20Coup%3A%20A%20History%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Deep%20State%3C%2Fem%3E%20closely%20looks%20at%20bias%20that%20runs%20deep%20in%20the%20Indian%20security%20establishment%20against%20the%20Muslim%20community.%20Ganpatye%2C%20a%20Mumbai-based%20journalist%2C%20recently%20came%20out%20with%20her%20debut%20book%20%3Cem%3EWho%20Will%20Bell%20The%20Cow%3F%3A%20Beef%20Ban%3A%20Decoding%20its%20cultural%2C%20social%2C%20and%20economical%20aspects%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHow%20to%20Win%20an%20Indian%20Election%3A%20What%20Political%20Parties%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Want%20You%20to%20Know%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0book%20looks%20at%20political%20campaigns%20and%20disinformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThis%20is%20how%20my%20book%20%E2%80%9CWho%20Will%20Bell%20The%20Cow%3F%E2%80%9D%20was%20withdrawn%20for%20Vidarbha%20Lit%20Fest.%20I%20appreciate%20the%20honesty%20of%20the%20organisers%20to%20admit%20the%20pressure%20and%20come%20out%20open%20about%20it.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F6vkW9mnaR8%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F6vkW9mnaR8%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Shruti%20Ganapatye%20(%40shrutiganapatye)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fshrutiganapatye%2Fstatus%2F1710952843354738998%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%208%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChaudhary%20said%20that%20the%20decision%20came%20in%20following%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20some%20major%20sponsors%20of%20the%20festival.%20The%20initial%20objection%2C%20Chaudhary%20confirmed%2C%20was%20raised%20against%20more%20than%20four%20speakers.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20somehow%20salvaged%20the%20situation%20and%20managed%20to%20convince%20them%20(the%20sponsors).%20But%20they%20refused%20to%20be%20convinced%20about%20the%20four%20important%20speakers%20at%20the%20event%2C%E2%80%9D%20Choudhary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20added%20that%20the%20curators%E2%80%99%20family%20members%20were%20approached%20by%20right-wing%20persons.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20pressure%20was%20built%20from%20different%20sides.%20When%20they%20felt%20we%20might%20not%20budge%20if%20the%20sponsors%20withdrew%20and%20try%20to%20personally%20raise%20funds%2C%20our%20families%20were%20approached%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChaudhary%2C%20Sarda%20and%20Dharamadhikari%20had%20a%20decision%20to%20make.%20Whether%20to%20let%20go%20of%20the%20independence%20in%20running%20the%20festival%20or%20step%20down.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20situation%20that%20we%20found%20ourselves%20in%2C%20only%20the%20latter%20was%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chaudhary%20said.%20This%2C%20the%20curators%20say%2C%20happened%20as%20they%20could%20not%20have%20managed%20to%20run%20the%20show%20without%20sponsors%20supporting%20them.%20%E2%80%9CThose%20who%20withdrew%20actually%20were%20funding%20over%2060%25%20of%20the%20total%20budget%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chaudhary%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20festival%20idea%20was%20mooted%20to%20focus%20on%20non-fiction%20writers.%20In%202020%20too%2C%20many%20writers%2C%20known%20for%20their%20critical%20take%20on%20the%20current%20dispensation%2C%20were%20invited%20to%20the%20festival.%20%E2%80%9CLike%20say%20Akshaya%20Mukul%20was%20one%20of%20the%20speakers.%20But%20that%20time%2C%20the%20festival%20was%20not%20as%20well%20known.%20It%20was%20our%20first%20attempt%20to%20bring%20writers%20together.%20And%20we%20managed%20without%20any%20pushback%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chaudhary%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20who%20exactly%20had%20approached%20them%2C%20their%20families%20or%20the%20sponsors%2C%20Chaudhary%20refused%20to%20name%20names.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20writers%E2%80%99%20community%20is%20very%20small%20here%20in%20Nagpur%20and%20we%20get%20easily%20identified%20and%20targeted.%20It%20has%20taken%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20courage%20to%20publicly%20announce%20that%20we%20have%20stepped%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696941033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10163925%2Fbanner-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fvidarbha-literary-festival-curators-organiser-step-down-after-right-wing-threats%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sources%20privy%20to%20the%20developments%20at%20the%20festival%20said%20that%20activists%20belonging%20to%20right-wing%20organisations%20raised%20objection%20over%20four%20of%20the%20many%20speakers%20who%20were%20invited%20to%20the%20festival.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fvidarbha-literary-festival-curators-organiser-step-down-after-right-wing-threats%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RBI%20suspends%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20from%20adding%20new%20customers%20to%20mobile%20app%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696939923000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2019-11%2F09%2Ffull%2F1573248456-3381.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frbi-suspends-onboarding-of-new-customers-into-bank-of-baroda-s-mobile-app-123101000899_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lender%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20add%20customers%20to%20'bob%20World'%20after%20rectifying%20deficiencies%2C%20says%20regulator%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frbi-suspends-onboarding-of-new-customers-into-bank-of-baroda-s-mobile-app-123101000899_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frbi-suspends-onboarding-of-new-customers-into-bank-of-baroda-s-mobile-app-123101000899_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frbi-suspends-onboarding-of-new-customers-into-bank-of-baroda-s-mobile-app-123101000899_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Seeks%20Recall%20of%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Order%26nbsp%3BPermitting%20Married%20Woman%20To%20Terminate%2026-Week%20Pregnancy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F18171021%2Fpregnant-woman-under-cloudy-sky-in-silhouette-photography-1717292.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20doctors%20at%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20October%2010%2C%20expressed%20their%20inability%20to%20terminate%20a%20viable%2026-week%20pregnancy%20of%20a%20married%20mother%2C%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20hour-long%20hearing%20which%20involved%20an%20online%20interaction%20with%20the%20petitioner-mother%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20B.V.Nagarathna%20had%20on%20Monday%20allowed%20the%20mother%20to%20get%20her%20pregnancy%20terminated%20on%20mental%20health%20grounds%2C%20despite%20the%20AIIMS%20Medical%20Board%20advising%20against%20abortion%20in%20view%20of%20its%20finding%20that%20it%20is%20a%20viable%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%20sought%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20directions%20for%20recall%20of%20the%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20Kohli-Nagarathna%20bench%20on%20Monday%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20AIIMS%20doctors%E2%80%99%20moral%20dilemma%20to%20terminate%20a%20viable%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%2C%20after%20a%20brief%20hearing%20at%204%20pm%2C%20asked%20Bhati%20to%20submit%20a%20written%20application%20for%20recall%20so%20that%20the%20same%20bench%20which%20passed%20the%20order%20for%20abortion%20on%20Monday%20could%20be%20requested%20to%20consider%20it%20on%20Wednesday%20morning.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20an%20unprecedented%20hearing%20twice%20%E2%80%93%20once%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20again%20in%20the%20afternoon%20%E2%80%93%20to%20hear%20the%20pregnant%20married%20woman%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Ewho%20did%20not%20want%20to%20proceed%20with%20her%20third%20pregnancy%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20she%20would%20not%20be%20mentally%20fit%20to%20foster%20the%20child.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Kohli%20and%20Nagarathna%20spoke%20to%20the%20petitioner-mother%20and%20her%20husband%20online%2C%20to%20ascertain%20her%20wishes%20and%20satisfy%20the%20court%20that%20the%20couple%20voluntarily%20opted%20to%20abort%20the%20child%2C%20despite%20the%20AIIMS%20Medical%20Board%20certifying%20that%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20viable.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner-woman%20who%20sought%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20to%20abort%20her%20pregnancy%20in%20view%20of%20Section%203(2)%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.mohfw.gov.in%2F%3Fq%3Dacts-rules-and-standards-health-sector%2Facts%2Fmtp-act-1971%5C%22%3EMedical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20(MTP)%20Act%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20permits%20abortion%20only%20before%2020%20weeks%20of%20pregnancy%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20%E2%80%9Crisk%20of%20grave%20injury%20to%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20physical%20or%20mental%20health%20or%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20there%20is%20a%20substantial%20risk%20that%20the%20child%20would%20suffer%20from%20physical%20or%20mental%20abnormalities%20to%20be%20seriously%20handicapped%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20she%20was%20suffering%20from%20lactational%20amenorrhea%20(which%20causes%20a%20temporary%20absence%20of%20menstruation%20in%20lactating%20mothers)%20and%20post-partum%20depression%20(a%20medical%20condition%20that%20many%20women%20experience%20after%20having%20a%20baby%2C%20with%20feelings%20of%20sadness%2C%20anxiety%20and%20tiredness).%20The%20couple%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20raise%20a%20third%20child%20because%20of%20family%20and%20financial%20conditions%2C%20the%20petitioner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20first%20child%20of%20the%20couple%20is%20four%20years%20old%2C%20while%20the%20second%20child%20is%20one%20year%20old.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%2C%20the%20bench%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20was%20concerned%20more%20about%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20health%20and%20not%20that%20of%20the%20child.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20wanted%20to%20understand%20the%20context%2C%20that%20is%2C%20this%20is%20the%20case%20of%20a%20married%20couple%2C%20and%20not%20one%20of%20forced%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20added%20that%20it%20had%20no%20issue%20if%20the%20mother%20wanted%20to%20continue%20her%20pregnancy%2C%20but%20it%20underlined%20that%20she%20must%20have%20the%20willpower%20and%20emotional%20strength%20to%20do%20so.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20observed%20that%20the%20state%20is%20not%20going%20to%20help%20her%20after%20the%20delivery%20of%20the%20child%2C%20which%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20failure%20of%20family%20planning%20methods.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20morning%20hearing%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%20that%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20aborted%20to%20avoid%20giving%20birth%20to%20an%20unwanted%20child.%20The%20bench%20decided%20to%20give%20time%20till%201%20pm%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20mother%20wants%20to%20continue%20her%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%201%20pm%2C%20the%20petitioner%20made%20it%20clear%20to%20the%20bench%20through%20an%20online%20interaction%20that%20she%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20abortion%2C%20despite%20doctors%E2%80%99%20advice%20that%20she%20could%20give%20the%20child%20for%20adoption%20after%20delivery%20since%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20viable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20the%20contention%20that%20after%20the%2025th%20week%20of%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20mother%20could%20not%20be%20exercised%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20viable%20baby.%20But%20the%20bench%20emphasised%20that%20giving%20the%20child%20to%20adoption%20should%20also%20be%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20petitioner-mother.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20mother%20clearly%20said%20no%20to%20giving%20the%20child%20to%20adoption.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20found%20merit%20in%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20argument%20through%20her%20counsel%20that%20she%20was%20asking%20for%20her%20rights%20under%20Article%2021%20(protection%20of%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty)%2C%20which%20overrides%20the%20MTP%20Act.%20The%20additional%20solicitor%20general%2C%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%2C%20submitted%20that%20the%20bench%20had%20to%20balance%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20woman%20over%20her%20body%20with%20the%20right%20of%20the%20viable%20baby.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20Medical%20Board%20that%20the%20baby%20is%20viable%2C%20and%20can%20survive%20outside%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20womb%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20reasonable%20chance%20of%20survival%20of%20the%20child.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ayushman%20Bharat%2C%20health%20and%20wellness%20centres%2C%20union%20budget%202020%2C%20health%20budget%2C%20public%20healthcare%2C%20private%20healthcare%2C%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%2C%20AIIMS%2C%20NIMHANS%2C%20PGIMER%2C%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%2C%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Development%20Plan%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Regional%20Institute%20of%20Nursing%20and%20Paramedical%20Science%20Aizawl%2C%20nursing%2C%20nurses%2C%20hospital%20staff%2C%20National%20Health%20Policy%2C%20National%20Health%20Mission%2C%20primary%20care%2C%20secondary%20care%2C%20tertiary%20care%2C%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-393168%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAIIMS%2C%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bench%20wanted%20to%20know%20whether%20there%20is%20a%20reasonable%20chance%20of%20living%20for%20the%20child%20with%20dignity%20and%20nutrition%20and%20whether%20the%20couple%20can%20provide%20that.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20can%E2%80%99t%20force%20the%20petitioner-mother%20to%20give%20the%20child%20up%20for%20adoption%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20told%20the%20ASG%2C%20who%20contended%20that%20her%20right%20of%20autonomy%20ends%20once%20the%20fetus%20is%20viable.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20although%20the%20Medical%20Board%20opined%20that%20the%20child%20can%20survive%20if%20born%2C%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20of%20harm%20to%20the%20child%20because%20of%20the%20medicine%20that%20the%20petitioner-mother%20has%20been%20taking%20to%20treat%20her%20depression.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20husband%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20if%20she%20had%20to%20give%20birth%20to%20the%20child%2C%20they%20would%20rear%20it%2C%20and%20not%20give%20it%20for%20adoption%2C%20though%20he%20is%20concerned%20about%20her%20depression.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20wife%20should%20not%20suffer%2C%20and%20the%20child%20should%20not%20suffer%20from%20any%20abnormalities%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20bench.%20He%20said%20that%20as%20the%20Medical%20Board%20is%20silent%20on%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20condition%2C%20they%20cannot%20take%20care%20of%20the%20child%20if%20it%20is%20not%20healthy.%20As%20there%20is%20a%20risk%20that%20the%20child%2C%20if%20born%2C%20may%20be%20unwell%2C%20the%20couple%20preferred%20to%20abort%20the%20fetus.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalancing%20of%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20told%20the%20ASG%20that%20there%20is%20no%20competing%20right%20of%20an%20unborn%20child%20to%20be%20balanced%20with%20that%20of%20the%20petitioner-mother.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20held%20that%20it%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20citizens%20to%20adopt%20family%20planning%20methods%20to%20avoid%20giving%20birth%20to%20an%20unwanted%20child.%20The%20couple%20has%20a%20responsibility%20and%20can%E2%80%99t%20produce%20children%20like%20this%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%2C%20as%20it%20constitutes%20a%20burden%20on%20the%20country.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ASG%20pleaded%20with%20the%20bench%20to%20adjourn%20the%20hearing%20till%20Tuesday%2C%20to%20enable%20her%20to%20make%20submissions%20on%20balancing%20the%20right%20to%20life%20with%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20woman%20over%20her%20body.%20The%20ASG%20submitted%20that%20there%20can%20be%20no%20absolute%20right%20of%20autonomy%20of%20a%20woman%20over%20her%20body.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bench%20disagreed%20and%20said%20even%20a%20day%E2%80%99s%20delay%20would%20mean%20a%20setback%20to%20the%20mother.%20The%20bench%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20child%20may%20not%20survive%2C%20if%20born%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20kept%20in%20incubation.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20bench%20decided%20to%20give%20priority%20to%20the%20petitioner-mother%E2%80%99s%20mental%20health.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20reasoned%20that%20it%20has%20expansively%20interpreted%20Section%205%20of%20the%20MTP%20Act%20as%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20health%E2%80%9D%20has%20a%20broader%20connotation%20than%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20illness%E2%80%9D.%20Due%20to%20a%20delay%20in%20recognising%20pregnancy%20and%20changes%20in%20life%20circumstances%2C%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20pregnancy%20has%20become%20unwanted%20and%20unviable%2C%20the%20bench%20concluded.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20held%20that%20it%20took%20into%20account%20the%20decisional%20autonomy%20of%20the%20mother%20%E2%80%93%20including%20her%20physical%2C%20mental%2C%20financial%20and%20socio-economic%20background.%20The%20court%20has%20recognised%20the%20right%20of%20a%20woman%20over%20her%20body%2C%20and%20an%20unwanted%20child%20results%20in%20imposing%20the%20responsibility%20of%20rearing%20on%20the%20mother%2C%20when%20she%20does%20not%20consider%20herself%20fit%20to%20bear%20the%20onerous%20responsibility%2C%20the%20bench%20concluded.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20directed%20that%20in%20the%20event%20of%20the%20procedure%20for%20abortion%20to%20be%20carried%20out%20on%20Tuesday%20morning%20resulting%20in%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20live%20child%2C%20it%20should%20be%20kept%20in%20incubation%2C%20and%20may%20be%20given%20in%20adoption%2C%20if%20advisable.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20reluctant%20to%20entertain%20petitions%20under%20Article%2032%2C%20when%20the%20petitioner%20had%20the%20option%20of%20approaching%20the%20high%20court%20for%20an%20efficacious%20remedy%20under%20Article%20226%20of%20the%20constitution.%20However%2C%20as%20time%20was%20running%20out%2C%20it%20was%20deemed%20appropriate%20to%20entertain%20her%20petition%2C%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221156%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01-300x187.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01-1024x638.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671125%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Central%20Wing%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20Subhashish%20Panigrahi%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELessons%20on%20family%20planning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20the%20present%20case%20has%20valuable%20lessons%20for%20married%20couples%2C%20who%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20more%20cautious%2C%20in%20preventing%20unplanned%20pregnancies%20by%20adopting%20family%20planning%20methods.%20As%20India%20is%20the%20most%20populated%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20striving%20to%20achieve%20socio-economic%20development%20within%20the%20limited%20means%20and%20resources%20that%20the%20state%20has%2C%20every%20couple%20has%20equal%20rights%20and%20obligations%20including%20that%20of%20rearing%20children%20with%20access%20to%20nutrition%2C%20good%20education%2C%20the%20court%20said.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20underlined%20the%20need%20to%20disseminate%20all%20the%20schemes%20floated%20by%20Central%20and%20state%20family%20planning%20agencies%20to%20avoid%20unwanted%20pregnancies%20in%20married%20couples%20so%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20adoption%20of%20adequate%20family%20planning%20measures%20does%20not%20result%20in%20a%20case%20like%20this.%20The%20bench%20learnt%20that%20the%20couple%20in%20this%20case%20was%20not%20aware%20of%20family%20planning%2C%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20adequate%20care%20to%20prevent%20an%20unwanted%20pregnancy.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20the%20silver%20lining%20in%20this%20case%2C%20as%20the%20mother-in-law%20of%20the%20petitioner%20supports%20the%20daughter-in-law%20in%20rearing%20her%20children.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20today%E2%80%99s%20urban%20nuclear%20family%2C%20joint%20family%20is%20mostly%20missing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20noted%20in%20its%20order.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20is%20not%20a%20forced%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20petitioner-mother%20has%20valid%20reasons%20to%20avoid%20an%20unwanted%20pregnancy%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20bench%20directed%20AIIMS%20to%20carry%20out%20her%20abortion%20on%20Tuesday%20morning%2C%20as%20desired%20by%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20reasons%20to%20be%20recorded%20separately%2C%20we%20allow%20the%20present%20writ%20petition%20with%20a%20direction%20issued%20to%20the%20petitioner%20to%20visit%20the%20Obstetrics%20and%20Gynaecology%20Department%2C%20AIIMS%2C%20New%20Delhi%20tomorrow%20morning%2C%20i.e.%2C%20on%2010th%20October%2C%202023.%C2%A0%20AIIMS%20shall%20admit%20the%20petitioner%20for%20her%20to%20undergo%20the%20procedure%20of%20termination%20of%20her%20pregnancy%20at%20the%20earliest%20with%20follow%20up%20as%20may%20be%20advised%20by%20the%20treating%20doctors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696939236000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F18171021%2Fpregnant-woman-under-cloudy-sky-in-silhouette-photography-1717292.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-seeks-recall-of-scs-order-permitting-married-woman-to-terminate-26-week-pregnancy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20AIIMS%20doctors%20expressed%20their%20inability%20to%20terminate%20a%20viable%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20government%20sought%20the%20recall%20of%20the%20order%20passed%20on%20Monday%20granting%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20abortion%20on%20mental%20health%20grounds.%20The%20same%20bench%20will%20consider%20the%20recall%20application%20on%C2%A0Wednesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engag