sts%20connected%20with%20the%20Indian%20news%20portal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20illustrates%20this%20shocking%20trend.%20More%20unsettling%20is%20the%20arrest%20of%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%2C%20its%20Editor-in-Chief%2C%20and%20Amith%20Chakravorty%2C%20its%20Head%20of%20Human%20Resources%2C%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20investigating%20them%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cterror%20case%20with%20Chinese%20links%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Indian%20media%20has%20reported%20that%20the%20police%20has%20blatantly%20disregarded%20the%20legally%20sanctioned%20procedures%20in%20arresting%20the%20senior%20journalist%20and%20his%20colleague.%C2%A0%20The%20authorities%20are%20yet%20to%20make%20known%20any%20material%20on%20the%20website%20with%20links%20to%20any%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20activity%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CChinese%20propaganda%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20join%20the%20progressive%20media%2C%20civil%20society%20organisations%20and%20activists%20in%20India%20to%20condemn%20in%20no%20uncertain%20terms%20this%20brazen%20attack%20by%20the%20government%20on%20the%20free%20media.%20Harassment%20and%20intimidation%20of%20the%20independent%20media%20by%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20police%20and%20state%20agencies%20for%20narrow%20political%20gains%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20trend%20in%20a%20country%20claimed%20to%20be%20the%20%E2%80%98Mother%20of%20Democracy.%E2%80%99%20Many%20commentators%20have%20likened%20this%20trend%20to%20the%20stifling%20times%20of%20the%20Emergency%20in%20India%20during%20the%201970s%2C%20although%20a%20State%20of%20Emergency%20has%20not%20been%20formally%20declared%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20recent%20weeks%2C%20journalists%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20too%2C%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20enormous%20pressure%2C%20by%20way%20of%20judicial%20harassment%2C%20police%20violence%2C%20online%20harassment%2C%20attacks%20at%20reporting%20assignments%2C%20and%20intimidation